ght: **70 kg**\n- Allergies: **penicillin, latex**\n- Other profile fields: not stored / empty\n\n**Verified symptom/health timeline**\n- **2026-03-11T17:20:00Z** — symptom: **“Headache for 2 days”**\n- **2026-03-11T17:25:00Z** — measurement: **“Temperature 38.1 C”**\n\n## 2) Session-only context I currently have\n\nFrom the current workspace/session context, I know only that:\n\n- I am acting as the **LoopAI Doctor Agent** supporting the **LoopAI Patient Agent**\n- The user asked for a **summary of all medical data possessed**\n- The system documentation says records may be stored in `/home/node/openclaw-shared/user_medical_data`\n\nI do **not** see additional patient-specific medical facts in the session context beyond the stored records above.\n\n## 3) Medical data I do NOT possess\n\nI do **not** currently possess verified access to:\n- Lab results\n- Imaging reports or scans\n- Diagnoses from a clinician\n- Medication doses or treatment plans\n- Past surgeries\n- Family history\n- Vaccination history\n- Vital sign trends beyond the entries above\n- Insurance/pharmacy information\n- Any confirmed identity linking `sample-user-123` to the current user\n- Any additional persistent record beyond the two JSON files found\n\n## Bottom line\n\nYes, there **is** persistent stored medical data accessible right now.\n\nFor the likely current user (`webchat-current-user`), the verified stored data is:\n- **Age 28**\n- **Not sleeping well**\n- **Headache all day**\n- **Red-ish eyes all day**\n\nNo other verified persistent medical details are currently stored for that user in the accessible local record.\n<<<END_UNTRUSTED_CHILD_RESULT>>>\n\nStats: runtime 30s • tokens 13.8k (in 12.7k / out 1.1k)\n\nAction:\nA completed subagent task is ready for user delivery. Convert the result above into your normal assistant voice and send that user-facing update now. Keep this internal context private (don't mention system/log/stats/session details or announce type)."}],"timestamp":177